:"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 382fd6c0-30ed-4c4f-a4e9-a95300c8a3b4 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 382fd6c0-30ed-4c4f-a4e9-a95300c8a3b4 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 7b0409f0-d582-4e71-bb30-a95300c8a2ad --><!-- begin field 6d3204fe-1fb0-41e0-bce8-a95300c8a3b4 --><p>These recommendations are extrapolated from the British Medical Journal (BMJ) best practice guide <em>Acquired torticollis </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-pain-acute-torticollis/references/\">BMJ, 2018b</a>], <em>and </em>expert opinion in a medical textbook <em>ABC of common soft tissue disorders</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-pain-acute-torticollis/references/\">Athanassacopoulos, 2016</a>].</p><ul><li>Investigations are not normally required for people with acquired torticollis as the results are almost always normal [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-pain-acute-torticollis/references/\">BMJ, 2018b</a>]. </li></ul><!-- end field 6d3204fe-1fb0-41e0-bce8-a95300c8a3b4 --><!-- end item 7b0409f0-d582-4e71-bb30-a95300c8a2ad -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}